  "market_context": "Analysis focuses on the daily candle's Power of Three (AMD) structure: Asia session forms accumulation range; London session manipulates (sweeps Asia low), creating the daily wick; New York session distributes higher, completing open-low-high-close daily OHLC.",
  "key_observation": "London session aggressively sweeps the Asia range low (manipulation phase), forming the daily candle’s wick, then price distributes higher through NY session, confirming a bullish daily structure.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the Asia session consolidation range as the accumulation phase before London open.",
    "Step 2: Observe London session initiating an aggressive downward move that sweeps the Asia low, forming a down-close candle and retesting the low — this is the manipulation leg.",
    "Step 3: Note the retest and close above the manipulation low, signaling change in state of delivery and setting up for distribution higher.",
    "Step 4: Anticipate distribution higher into NY session, targeting expansion beyond prior highs, consistent with open-low-high-close daily profile.",
    "Step 5: Confirm the daily candle closes high after NY session expansion, validating the AMD sequence: accumulation (Asia), manipulation (London sweep), distribution (NY rise)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade taken long above manipulation low after retest; price distributed higher through NY session, achieving multi-R gain.",
  "lessons": "London often manipulates the Asia range to create the daily wick; successful trades require identifying the manipulation low, waiting for retest + closure above it, then entering with bias toward NY distribution higher.",
